By the time of his death almost the whole of Ireland is said to have been converted to Christianity. He is also credited with codifying the laws of Ireland. In his Latin autobiography, as well as in later tradition, his name appears as <i>Patricius</i> ‘patrician’ (i.e. belonging to the Roman senatorial or noble class), but this may actually represent a Latinized form of some lost Celtic (British) name. In Ireland in particular, it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1355923,"age":27,"year":"1167","julianDay":2147298,"description":"Arrival of Normans at Baginbun in Co. Wexford thus started 800 year struggle between English and Irish.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Patrick Plunkett was born about 1140, in Ireland as the son of Richard Dubh Plunkett. He had at least 2 sons."},"et":{"about 1140–":"umbes 1140–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1167":"1167","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","Ireland":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 1140–":"noin 1140–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","about 1140":"noin 1140","1167":"1167","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","Ireland":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"about 1140–":"environ 1140–Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","about 1140":"environ 1140","1167":"1167","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","Ireland":"Irlande","lifeSummary":"Patrick Plunkett est né environ 1140, à Irlande, fils de Richard Dubh Plunkett. Il a eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"about 1140–":"um 1140–Verstorben","1140–Male":"1140–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1160–Male":"1160–Verstorben","1170–Male":"1170–Verstorben","1120–Male":"1120–Verstorben